com.upsight.android.analytics.session

Interface UpsightSessionCallbacks


  • public interface UpsightSessionCallbacks
    Optionally implemented interface to allow hooks into Upsight session creation.

    An implementation must have its full class path specified in the Android Manifest as meta-data with android:name="com.upsight.session_callbacks". You may only register one implementation of UpsightSessionCallbacks.

    • Method Detail

      • onStart

        void onStart(UpsightSessionContext upsight,
             UpsightSessionInfo previousSessionInfo)
        Called when a new session is about to start. It is guaranteed to run before any event is recorded, so this gives an opportunity for the application to set initial event attributes.

        This block is executed synchronously when UpsightContext is created and should be fast-returning. You also must not attempt creating another UpsightContext here, as that would result in this callback being triggered again, and again, recursively, until we overflow the stack, and nobody likes that.

        Parameters:
        upsight - A UpsightSessionContext that fulfills the subset of Upsight SDK APIs which accept it as a parameter.
        previousSessionInfo - Information about the previous Upsight session. If there is no previous session, UpsightSessionInfo.NONE is passed.

      • onStarted

        void onStarted(UpsightContext upsight)
        Called when a new session is created. An UpsightSessionStartEvent has been recorded and you can call the full set of Upsight SDK APIs here.

        This block is executed synchronously when UpsightContext is created and should be fast-returning. You also must not attempt creating another UpsightContext here, as that would result in this callback being triggered again, and again, recursively, until we overflow the stack, and nobody likes that.

        Parameters:
        upsight - The UpsightContext.

      • onResume

        void onResume(UpsightSessionContext upsight,
              UpsightSessionInfo resumedSessionInfo)
        Called when an existing session is about to be extended. It is guaranteed to run before any event is recorded in this extended part of the session, so this gives an opportunity for the application to set initial event attributes.

        This block is executed synchronously when UpsightContext is created and should be fast-returning. You also must not attempt creating another UpsightContext here, as that would result in this callback being triggered again, and again, recursively, until we overflow the stack, and nobody likes that.

        Parameters:
        upsight - A UpsightSessionContext that fulfills the subset of Upsight SDK APIs which accept it as a parameter.
        resumedSessionInfo - Information about the extended Upsight session.

      • onResumed

        void onResumed(UpsightContext upsight)
        Called when an existing session is extended. An UpsightSessionResumeEvent has been recorded and you can call the full set of Upsight SDK APIs here.

        This block is executed synchronously when UpsightContext is created and should be fast-returning. You also must not attempt creating another UpsightContext here, as that would result in this callback being triggered again, and again, recursively, until we overflow the stack, and nobody likes that.

        Parameters:
        upsight - The UpsightContext.
